==English==

===Etymology===
From scientific {{etyl|la|en}} ''[[Onchocerca]]'' (a genus of parasitic worms), from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|ὄγκος||barb}} + {{m|grc|κέρκος||tail}} + ''[[-iasis]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɒŋkəsɜːˈkaɪəsɪs/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|onchocerciases}}

# {{lb|en|medicine}} A disease caused by a [[worm]] of the genus ''[[Onchocerca]]'', especially as transmitted to humans by flies and often causing [[blindness]]; common in tropical Africa.

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|river blindness}}
* {{l|en|Robles' disease}}

